            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20636",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tbarstow",
                        "name": "tbarstow",
                        "displayName": "Taylor Barstow",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The fix to ZF-1325 is the source of this issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tbarstow",
                        "name": "tbarstow",
                        "displayName": "Taylor Barstow",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-02T08:38:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-02T08:38:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/21290",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is actually the intended behavior.  \n\nIn fact, Zend_Loader shouldnt be throwing warnings or errors, and there is a new verison in the incubator that supresses those issues.\n\nI'm gonna wait on this.\n\n--\n\nUpdating project management info.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-22T10:45:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-22T10:45:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/22294",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=flo",
                        "name": "flo",
                        "displayName": "Florian Hoenig",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "I found the same problem. Have a custom savehandler, which uses Zend_XmlRpc_Client. This somewhere down the chain uses Zend_Validate_Hostname and for a .com address it tried to do Zend_Loader::isReadible(\"Zend\/Validate\/Hostname\/Com.php\"), which does not exist. isReadible tried to @fopen and surpress the warning when it does NOT exist. Which is fine, except the above error handler seems to ignore the \"@\" in front of the fread. \n\nThis renders Zend_XmlRpc_Client unusable within a session savehandler callback !!\n\nZF 1.5.2 that is. and php 5.2.1  through php 5.2.6 is what I tried. I when through all possible php.ini settings, but could not figure out how to make Zend_Session::start() respect the @ in Zend_Loader.\n\nAny glue?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=flo",
                        "name": "flo",
                        "displayName": "Florian Hoenig",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2008-06-10T13:53:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-06-10T13:53:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25584",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=studio24",
                        "name": "studio24",
                        "displayName": "Simon R Jones",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've been looking into ZF-2900 which is related.\n\nThe underlying problem is that if a custom error handler is used then this will always receive errors, even when they are suppressed. The solution is to update the code in Zend_Session_Exception::handleSessionStartError as so:\n\n{code}\nstatic public function handleSessionStartError($errno, $errstr, $errfile, $errline, $errcontext)\n    {\n    \t\/\/ Do not throw an exception if this is a suppressed error - see ZF-3020\n    \tif (error_reporting() === 0) {\n    \t    \treturn;\n    \t}\n        self::$sessionStartError = $errfile . '(Line:' . $errline . '): Error #' . $errno . ' ' . $errstr . ' ' . $errcontext;\n    }\n{code}\n\nI can make this change myself if given SVN commit rights to the Zend\/Session folder\n\nbest wishes,\nSimon",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=studio24",
                        "name": "studio24",
                        "displayName": "Simon R Jones",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-02T07:17:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-02T07:17:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27955",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Will reevaluate within 2 weeks.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-10T09:34:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-10T09:34:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28026",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mratzloff",
                        "name": "mratzloff",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Ratzloff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "WHAT THE F^H^H^H^H^H^H^H^H^H^HI would really appreciate it if this were fixed.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mratzloff",
                        "name": "mratzloff",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Ratzloff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-10T14:05:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-10T14:05:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28027",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mratzloff",
                        "name": "mratzloff",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Ratzloff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "To add more information to my previous outburst,\n\nWarning: array_key_exists() [function.array-key-exists]: The first argument should be either a string or an integer in \/usr\/lib64\/php\/ZendFramework-1.7.1\/library\/Zend\/Filter\/Input.php on line 429\n\nFatal error: Exception thrown without a stack frame in Unknown on line 0\n\nDisappears when Zend_Session::start() is commented out.\n\nThanks Ralph",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mratzloff",
                        "name": "mratzloff",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Ratzloff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-10T14:12:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-10T14:12:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28028",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mratzloff",
                        "name": "mratzloff",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Ratzloff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "(sigh)  Sorry, everyone.  It turns out it was my own dumb fault.  There was a bug in our custom save handler.  After two hours trying to debug this, my eyes were going cross-eyed.  My apologies.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mratzloff",
                        "name": "mratzloff",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Ratzloff",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-10T14:46:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-10T14:46:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30062",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gnarfle",
                        "name": "gnarfle",
                        "displayName": "Chad Cunningham",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "So is the 1.8 suppress warnings going to fix this? And is there any chance of it being fixed in the 1.7 branch? I've hacked ZendSession to get around this which I hate doing, but this bug is a royal pain.\n\nI'm using Doctrine with ZF, and doctrine does a lot of on the fly class generation. Zend autoloader tries to load these classes when it doesn't need to, however I can easily suppress these warnings by setting error reporting and the app works great. That is, until I try to save a Doctrine object in the session. Since Zend Session believes that I don't know what I want my error reporting to be and throws an exception for every little warning or notice, it will grind the app to a halt for a problem that I've configured the app to ignore.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gnarfle",
                        "name": "gnarfle",
                        "displayName": "Chad Cunningham",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-09T13:50:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-09T13:50:04.000+0000"
                },
